> 
> Estimates vary, but it is generally agreed that there would be a continued warming trend for several decades to centuries even after emissions stop. The exact duration and extent of this continued warming would depend on various factors, including the amount of CO$_2$ already in the atmosphere, the response of the oceans and ice masses, and feedback mechanisms in the climate system.
> 
> It's important to note that this continued warming highlights the importance of taking proactive measures to reduce greenhouse gas emissions and limit global warming. Even if we were to stop emissions today, the impacts of past and present emissions would still be felt for an extended period, underscoring the urgency of mitigating climate change.
